query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `evidenceChains` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT NOT NULL,
  `userId` int NOT NULL,
  `evidenceId` varchar(64) NOT NULL,
  `documentId` int,
  `originalFilename` varchar(512) NOT NULL,
  `originalHash` varchar(64) NOT NULL,
  `mimeType` varchar(128),
  `fileSize` int,
  `chainData` text NOT NULL,
  `isVerified` enum('true','false') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'true',
  `verificationErrors` text,
  `metadata` text,
  `createdAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updatedAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `evidenceChains_evidenceId_idx` (`evidenceId`),
  KEY `evidenceChains_userId_idx` (`userId`),
  KEY `evidenceChains_originalHash_idx` (`originalHash`),
  CONSTRAINT `evidenceChains_userId_fk` FOREIGN KEY (`userId`) REFERENCES `users` (`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  CONSTRAINT `evidenceChains_documentId_fk` FOREIGN KEY (`documentId`) REFERENCES `documents` (`id`) ON DELETE SET NULL
);
